================================================================================
1. PROJECT OVERVIEW
================================================================================

Magisk is a suite of open-source tools for Android that provides:
  - Root access management (su)
  - Systemless modifications via modules
  - Zygisk: Zygote injection for module code in app processes
  - DenyList: Hide root/Magisk from selected apps
  - Boot image patching
  - SELinux policy manipulation

The project uses a UNIQUE ARCHITECTURE:
  - Native code is a HYBRID of Rust and C++, linked via the CXX crate
  - Rust handles all high-level logic; C++ handles low-level syscall wrappers
  - The Android app is written in Kotlin + Java with MVVM architecture
  - The build system is 3-layer: Python orchestrator -> NDK + Cargo -> Gradle

MATURE AND STABLE - Magisk is one of the most widely used Android root solutions.


