================================================================================
3. BUILD SYSTEM
================================================================================

3.1 Build Prerequisites
-----------------------
  - Python 3.8+
  - Android NDK (custom ONDK distribution or standard NDK r28+)
  - Rust toolchain (with Android targets installed)
  - JDK 17+ for Gradle
  - Gradle (wrapper included)

  ABIs supported: armeabi-v7a, arm64-v8a, x86, x86_64, riscv64

3.2 Build Commands
-------------------
  All builds are driven through build.py:

    python build.py <command> [options]

  Commands:
    all          Build everything: native + app + stub
    native       Build all native binaries (Rust + C++)
    app          Build Android APKs (requires native binaries first)
    stub         Build stub APK only
    test         Build and run tests
    clean        Clean all build outputs
    ndk          Download/setup the custom ONDK distribution
    emulator     Build emulator image
    avd_patch    Patch AVD system image
    cargo        Run cargo commands directly
    clippy       Run clippy lints on Rust code
    gen          Code generation

3.3 Build Flow
---------------

  Step 1: python build.py native

    [Rust Build]                          [C++ Build]
       |                                      |
  cargo build for each crate:            ndk-build using Android.mk:
     magisk (core)                         Links Rust .a files
     magiskboot (boot)                     + base.cpp, applets.cpp
     magiskinit (init)                     + su.cpp, zygisk/*
     magiskpolicy (sepolicy)               + bootimg.cpp
       |                                    + init/*.cpp
       v                                    + sepolicy/*
  Output: *.a static libs                  + external/*
       |                                      |
       +----------+--------------------------+
                  |
                  v
        elf-cleaner (strip sections)
                  |
                  v
        Native binaries in native/out/{abi}/
        (magisk, magiskinit, magiskboot, magiskpolicy, libinit-ld.so)

  Step 2: python build.py app

    Gradle assembleRelease via MagiskPlugin:
      1. Loads config.prop + gradle.properties
      2. Copies native binaries from native/out/{abi} into JNI libs
      3. Downloads busybox
      4. Copies shell scripts into assets/
      5. Embeds stub.apk into assets/
      6. Generates stub APK with randomized class names
      7. Signs APK with config.prop keystore
      8. Adds version comment to APK via AddCommentTask
                  |
                  v
        out/app-release.apk
        out/stub-release.apk

3.4 Build Artifacts
--------------------
  out/
  |-- app-release.apk        # Full Magisk Manager APK (~30-50MB)
  |-- app-debug.apk          # Debug variant
  |-- stub-release.apk       # Stub APK (~10KB)
  +-- stub-debug.apk

  native/out/{abi}/
  |-- magisk                 # Main executable (daemon + su + resetprop)
  |-- magiskinit             # Init replacement (static binary)
  |-- magiskboot             # Boot image tool (static binary)
  |-- magiskpolicy           # SELinux policy tool
  |-- libinit-ld.so          # LD_PRELOAD shared library
  +-- lib*.a                 # Rust static libraries


================================================================================
4. NATIVE COMPONENTS (C++ / Rust)
================================================================================

4.1 magisk (Daemon + CLI + su + resetprop + zygisk + denylist)
---------------------------------------------------------------
  Source:   native/src/core/
  Binary:   magisk
  Language: Rust (core logic) + C++ (entry, syscalls, zygisk hooks)
  Linking:  Static linking via CXX crate

  Architecture:
    applets.cpp: main()
        |
        +--> argv[0] contains applet name (symlink detection)
        |
        +-- "magisk"    -> magisk_main() [magisk.rs]
        |       Handles commands:
        |         --daemon        Start magiskd
        |         --post-fs-data  Boot stage 1
        |         --service       Boot stage 2 (late_start)
        |         --boot-complete Boot stage 3
        |         --install-module [zip]
        |         --remove-modules
        |         --unlock-boot-image
        |         --preinit-rc    Generate init.rc overlay
        |
        +-- "su"        -> su_client_main() [su/su.cpp]
        |       Parses -c, -t, -Z, -g, -G flags
        |       Connects to magiskd via Unix socket
        |       Sends SuRequest, waits for decision
        |       If allowed: fork, switch mount ns, drop caps, exec shell
        |
        +-- "resetprop" -> resetprop_main() [resetprop/ cli.rs]
        |       Read/write/delete system properties
        |       Bypasses property_service for direct property area access
        |       Supports --file for persistent props
        |
        +-- "magisk32/64" -> magisk_main() (force 32/64-bit mode)
        |
        +-- "zygisk"    -> zygisk_main() [zygisk/entry.cpp]
                Starts zygisk daemon (NativeBridgeItf)

  DAEMON (daemon.rs):
    - Creates Unix socket at $MAGISKTMP/.magisk/device/socket
    - Thread pool for handling connections
    - Request types (enum with Encodable/Decodable):
        CHECK_VERSION
        START_DAEMON / STOP_DAEMON
        POST_FS_DATA / LATE_START / BOOT_COMPLETE
        SUPERUSER (su auth)
        SQLITE_CMD (DB operations)
        DENYLIST (add/remove/list)
        ZYGOTE_RESTART
        REMOVE_MODULES
        ZYGISK (companion communication)

  BOOT STAGES (bootstages.rs):
    post-fs-data:
      - Mount tmpfs at $MAGISKTMP
      - Initialize SELinux contexts
      - Load and mount modules
      - Execute post-fs-data scripts
      - Safe mode detection (volume down key)
    late_start:
      - Execute service-mode scripts
    boot_complete:
      - Reset bootloop counter
      - Ensure manager APK is installed

  MODULE SYSTEM (module.rs):
    - Scans /data/adb/modules/*/
    - Reads module.prop for metadata
    - Builds a virtual filesystem tree:
        For each module:
          - system/    -> overlay on /system/*
          - vendor/    -> overlay on /vendor/*
          - system_ext/ -> overlay on /system_ext/*
          - product/   -> overlay on /product/*
          - sepolicy.rule -> SELinux policy injection
          - zygisk/    -> Zygisk native libs
          - .replace   -> Whiteout (hide original file)
          - update.json -> Online update metadata
          - disable    -> Flag file to disable
          - remove     -> Flag file to delete on reboot
          - skip_mount -> Flag to skip mounting
    - Applies bind mounts for file replacements
    - Injects magisk bins into PATH
    - Injects lib*.so into /system/lib* for Zygisk

4.2 magiskinit (Init Replacement)
-----------------------------------
  Source:   native/src/init/
  Binary:   magiskinit
  Language: Rust (high-level) + C++ (mounting, patching)
  Purpose:  Replaces /init in the boot image ramdisk

  Key Behaviors:
    1. If invoked as "magisk" -> magisk_proxy_main() (for SELinux context)
    2. If PID == 1 -> MagiskInit::new().start()

  Boot Mode Detection:
    - Parses /proc/cmdline, /proc/device-tree, /sys/block
    - Checks for androidboot.slot_suffix (AB slots)
    - Checks for androidboot.verifiedbootstate
    - Checks root directory type (overlayfs, tmpfs, ext4)

  Boot Paths:
    [2-Stage Init (2SI)] - Modern devices:
      first_stage()
        -> hijack_init_with_switch_root()
           [Uses /sdcard trick: binds magiskinit as /sdcard
            so Android SwitchRoot mounts it as /system/bin/init]
        -> second_stage()
           [Patches root, injects init.rc, starts magiskd]

    [Legacy System-as-Root (SAR)]:
      legacy_system_as_root()
        -> hexpatches /init to re-exec as magiskinit

    [RootFS] - Old devices:
      rootfs()
        -> patch_rw_root() directly patches root directory

    [Recovery/Charger]:
      -> restore original init, continue normal boot

  Key Operations:
    - Mounts tmpfs for $MAGISKTMP
    - Injects init.rc services:
        magisk --post-fs-data
        magisk --service
        magisk --boot-complete
    - Creates overlay filesystem structure
    - Extracts magisk.xz, stub.xz, init-ld.xz from ramdisk
    - LD_PRELOAD: libinit-ld.so intercepts security_load_policy()

  Ramdisk Structure (after patching):
    /
    |-- init -> magiskinit         (replaces /init)
    |-- overlay.d/
        +-- sbin/
            |-- magisk.xz          (compressed magisk daemon)
            |-- stub.xz            (compressed stub.apk)
            +-- init-ld.xz         (compressed LD_PRELOAD library)

4.3 magiskboot (Boot Image Tool)
---------------------------------
  Source:   native/src/boot/
  Binary:   magiskboot
  Language: Rust (90%) + C++ (bootimg parsing)
  Purpose:  Unpack, modify, and repack Android boot images

  Subcommands:
    unpack <image>      Extract boot image components
    repack <dir>        Repack boot image from extracted components
    verify <image>     Verify boot image signature
    sign <image>       Sign boot image (AVB 1.0)
    extract <payload>  Extract boot from OTA payload.bin
    hexpatch <file> <from> <to>   Binary hex patch
    cpio <cpio> <cmd>   Manipulate CPIO archives (add/remove/extract/test)
    dtb <dtb> <cmd>     Patch device tree blob
    split <file>       Split file by format boundaries
    sha1 <file>        Compute SHA1 hash
    cleanup            Remove temp files
    compress <type> <file>    Compress file
    decompress <type> <file>  Decompress file

  Boot Image Formats Supported:
    - AOSP standard boot image
    - AOSP vendor_boot
    - ChromeOS (with futility)
    - DHTB (Droid HiSilicon)
    - BLOB (Samsung)
    - MTK header
    - AVB footer / vbmeta

  Key Capabilities:
    - bootimg.cpp: Header parsing (page size, kernel/ramdisk offsets)
    - cpio.rs: Ramdisk CPIO manipulation (add magiskinit, overlay.d)
    - dtb.rs: DTB patching (remove verify/encrypt from fstab)
    - compress.rs: Multi-format compression/decompression
    - sign.rs: AVB 1.0 signing (SHA1/SHA256/RSA)
    - payload.rs: OTA payload.bin extraction (protobuf-based)
    - patch.rs: Binary hex search/replace within files
    - format.rs: Automatic format detection

4.4 magiskpolicy (SELinux Policy Tool)
---------------------------------------
  Source:   native/src/sepolicy/
  Binary:   magiskpolicy
  Language: Rust (CLI) + C++ (policy engine)
  Purpose:  Load, modify, compile, and apply SELinux policies

  Operations (CLI commands):
    --live              Apply to live kernel policy
    --load <file>       Load policy file
    --save <file>       Save policy file
    allow <s> <t> <c> <p>     Add allow rule
    deny <s> <t> <c> <p>      Add deny rule
    auditallow <s> <t> <c> <p>
    dontaudit <s> <t> <c> <p>
    allowxperm <s> <t> <c> <r>
    permissive <type>           Set domain permissive
    enforce <type>              Set domain enforcing
    type <name>                 Add type
    attribute <name>            Add attribute
    type_transition <s> <t> <c> <d>
    genfscon <fs> <path> <ctx>  Add genfscon
    --apply                    Apply rules to loaded policy

  Internals:
    - Uses libsepol for policy database manipulation
    - Can compile split CIL policies
    - Reads/writes binary policydb files
    - Injects rules at runtime via /sys/fs/selinux/load

4.5 libbase (Shared Base Library)
-----------------------------------
  Source:   native/src/base/
  Language: Rust + C++ (dual implementations, bridges via CXX)
  Used by:  ALL native binaries

  C++ Base (base.cpp):
    - mmap_data() / mmap_data_rw(): Memory-mapped file I/O
    - LOGx() macros: Logging (debug/info/warn/error)
    - exec_command() / exec_command_sync(): Process execution
    - new_daemon_thread(): Thread creation
    - switch_mnt_ns(): Mount namespace switching
    - split() / replace_all() / parse_int(): String utilities
    - fork_dont_care() / fork_no_orphan(): Fork helpers

  Rust Base (lib.rs + modules):
    - Utf8CStr / Utf8CString: Safe UTF-8 C-string types
    - Directory / DirEntry: Filesystem traversal
    - MappedFile: Safe mmap wrapper
    - MountInfo: /proc/self/mountinfo parser
    - FsPathBuilder: Path construction utility
    - argh: Argument parsing library
    - Result types with error handling

4.6 External Libraries
-----------------------
  All built from source via NDK (Android.mk):

  libxz (xz-embedded):
    - XZ decompression (used by magiskinit for ramdisk decompression)

  liblz4:
    - LZ4 compression (used by magiskboot for boot image decompression)

  libsepol (from SELinux upstream):
    - Full SELinux policy library (used by magiskpolicy)
    - Includes CIL compiler

  liblsplt:
    - PLT hooking library (used by Zygisk for function interception)
    - Cross-platform ELF hooking

  libsystemproperties:
    - Direct system property area manipulation (used by resetprop)
    - Bypasses Android's property_service

  libcxx:
    - Minimal C++ runtime (new/delete operators)
    - Used when no full STL is available

  crt0:
    - Custom C runtime for static binaries
    - Enables static linking without glibc dependency


================================================================================
5. ANDROID APP COMPONENTS (Kotlin/Java)
================================================================================

5.1 stub Module (~10KB Stub APK)
----------------------------------
  Source:   app/stub/
  Purpose:  Minimal APK that downloads the full Magisk Manager
            Installed when user first runs magisk or during boot

  Key Files:
    StubApplication.java     - Minimal Application class
    DelegateComponentFactory.java - Generates placeholder components
    ClassLoaders.java        - Custom class loading for real APK
    DynLoad.java             - Dynamic loading orchestration
    DownloadActivity.java    - Downloads full APK from configured URL
    StubRootService.java     - Stub root service entry

  How it works:
    1. StubApplication sets up component mapping from StubApk.Data
    2. DelegateComponentFactory creates dummy Activity/Service/Provider
    3. When launched, DownloadActivity connects to network
    4. Downloads full APK to internal storage
    5. Uses DexClassLoader to load real classes
    6. Transparently delegates app lifecycle to real APK

5.2 shared Module (Java Library - pro.magisk)
----------------------------------------------
  Source:   app/shared/
  Language: Java only (no Kotlin)
  Purpose:  APK loading and installation utilities

  Key Files:
    StubApk.java           - Dynamic APK loading (addAssetPath, resources)
    DynamicClassLoader.java - Custom class loader for stub->real switch
    APKInstall.java        - PackageInstaller Session API for silent install
    ProviderInstaller.java - ContentProvider-based APK installation
    CompoundEnumeration.java - Enumeration merging utility

5.3 core Module (Core Logic - pro.magisk.core)
-----------------------------------------------
  Source:   app/core/
  Language: Kotlin + Java
  Purpose:  Core business logic, data layer, services

  Key Files:
    App.kt                 - Application class (stub data initialization)
    AppContext.kt          - App context, root shell init
    Info.kt                - Magisk version/environment info
    Const.kt               - Constants (URLs, paths)
    Config.kt              - User preferences wrapper
    Hacks.kt               - SDK compatibility workarounds

  Services & Receivers:
    Service.kt             - Bound service for root operations
    JobService.kt          - JobScheduler background tasks
    Receiver.kt            - BroadcastReceiver (boot, package changes)
    Provider.kt            - ContentProvider (su logging, app comm)

  SU System:
    SuRequestHandler.kt    - Handle incoming su requests
    SuCallbackHandler.kt   - Process su callback intents

  Database (Room):
    MagiskDB.kt            - Room DB (policy, settings, strings, su_logs)
    PolicyDao.kt           - CRUD for su policies
    SettingsDao.kt         - Magisk settings
    SuLogDao.kt            - Superuser access logs
    StringDao.kt           - String key-value store

  Networking:
    NetworkService.kt      - Retrofit service for GitHub API
    DownloadEngine.kt      - File download with progress tracking
    DownloadProcessor.kt   - Download queue processor

5.4 apk Module (Full UI - pro.magisk)
---------------------------------------
  Source:   app/apk/
  Language: Kotlin + XML
  Purpose:  Full Magisk Manager user interface (MVVM)

  Architecture: Navigation Component + DataBinding + ViewModel + Material Design

  Screens (Fragments):
    HomeFragment.kt        - Dashboard: Magisk version, ramdisk, ABI
    InstallFragment.kt     - Install/upgrade Magisk (direct, patch, inactive slot)
    ModuleFragment.kt      - Module management (list, install, action buttons)
    SuperuserFragment.kt   - Manage app superuser permissions
    DenyListFragment.kt    - Configure DenyList (hide root from apps)
    LogFragment.kt         - View Magisk logs and su logs
    SettingsFragment.kt    - App and Magisk settings
    SuRequestActivity.kt   - Superuser request popup dialog
    FlashFragment.kt       - Flashing process console/log
    ThemeFragment.kt       - Theme selection (dark/light/system)

5.5 build_logic (Custom Gradle Plugin)
----------------------------------------
  Source:   app/build_logic/src/main/java/
  Language: Kotlin
  Purpose:  Custom Gradle plugin for Magisk APK building

  Key Files:
    Plugin.kt              - Applies plugin, loads config from config.prop
    Setup.kt               - setupCoreLib, setupMainApk, setupAppCommon
    Stub.kt                - Generates stub APK with randomized class names
    AddCommentTask.kt      - Adds version metadata as ZIP comment
    DesugarClassVisitorFactory.kt - Bytecode desugaring


================================================================================
6. HOW COMPONENTS LINK TOGETHER
================================================================================

6.1 Native <-> Native (Rust <-> C++ via CXX)
-----------------------------------------------
  All native binaries use the CXX crate for Rust/C++ FFI.

  Mechanism:
    #[cxx::bridge] modules in Rust define shared functions:
      - Rust functions callable from C++
      - C++ functions callable from Rust

  Example:
    Rust calls:    exec_root_shell() [C++ implemented]
    C++ calls:     get_magisk_tmp() [Rust implemented]

  At compile time:
    cargo build runs cxx-gen to generate C++ headers
    These headers are included by Android.mk C++ sources
    Both sides link into the same binary

6.2 Native <-> Java (Unix Sockets + libsu)
--------------------------------------------
  Primary IPC mechanism between magiskd and the Java app.

  Flow:
    magiskd (native):
      1. Creates Unix socket @ $MAGISKTMP/.magisk/device/socket
      2. Listens for connections from Java app
      3. Uses Encodable/Decodable trait for binary message serialization
      4. Supports SCM_RIGHTS file descriptor passing

    Java app (via libsu library):
      1. Connects to the socket using libsu's socket utilities
      2. Sends request codes and serialized parameters
      3. Receives responses

  libsu (topjohnwu's library):
    - Abstracts root shell access
    - Provides socket connection to magiskd
    - Handles shell command execution
    - Manages mount namespace separation

6.3 Native <-> Java (Zygisk JNI Hooks)
-----------------------------------------
  Zygisk injects code into Zygote process to intercept app forking.

  Mechanism:
    1. magiskinit sets ro.dalvik.vm.native.bridge=libzygisk.so
    2. Android Zygote calls LoadNativeBridge() which loads libzygisk.so
    3. libzygisk.so exposes NativeBridgeItf struct to Android
    4. On native bridge load, hook_entry() is called
    5. Zygisk performs PLT hooks on:
       - dlclose (prevent unloading)
       - strdup (detect ZygoteInit)
       - fork (intercept process creation)
       - unshare (intercept mount namespace isolation)
       - selinux_android_setcontext (intercept SELinux context)
       - pthread_attr_destroy (cleanup after fork)
    6. JNI method hooks replace:
       - com/android/internal/os/Zygote.nativeForkAndSpecialize()
       - com/android/internal/os/Zygote.nativeSpecializeAppProcess()
       - com/android/internal/os/Zygote.nativeForkSystemServer()
    7. In each app process: Zygisk decides whether to load modules
       based on denylist and process identity

  Zygisk Module API:
    - Modules provide lib/zygisk/arm64-v8a.so / armeabi-v7a.so
    - These implement ZygiskModule interface:
        onLoad(): Platform info
        onProcessList(processes): Filter app list
        onAppSpecialize(app_info): Per-app initialization
        onSystemServerSpecialize(server_info): System server init
    - Companion daemon (zygiskd) manages module companion entries

6.4 Native <-> Java (Content Providers)
-----------------------------------------
  For su request notifications and logging.

  Flow (su request):
    su client (native) -> magiskd (native)
      -> needs user decision (query mode)
      -> creates FIFO at $MAGISKTMP/.magisk/su_request_{PID}
      -> launches app via am start with extras
      -> app shows dialog, writes decision to FIFO
      -> daemon reads decision, proceeds or denies

  Flow (su logging):
    -> app's ContentProvider exposes su_logs URIs
    -> native daemon calls content provider insert()
    -> logs are stored in Room DB

6.5 Stub APK <-> Full APK
----------------------------
  1. Stub APK is initially installed (~10KB)
  2. On first launch, DownloadActivity downloads full APK
  3. Full APK is stored in internal storage/data
  4. DynamicClassLoader loads real APK classes
  5. DelegateComponentFactory maps stub components to real ones
  6. App seamlessly transitions to full version


