7.2 Boot Process Flowchart
-----------------------------

  [Power On]
       |
       v
  [BootROM -> Bootloader]
       |
       v
  [Linux Kernel]
       |
       v
  [Boot Image Loaded]
       |
       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  |           magiskinit (PID 1)               |
  |                                            |
  |  +--> Detect boot mode:                    |
  |  |    - Parse cmdline for androidboot.*    |
  |  |    - Check device tree                  |
  |  |    - Check /sys/block for partitions    |
  |  |                                         |
  |  +--> Choose path:                         |
  |       |                                    |
  |       +--- [2SI] first_stage():            |
  |       |     scan_partitions()              |
  |       |     hijack_init_with_switch_root() |
  |       |     (binds /sdcard as magiskinit)  |
  |       |       -> second_stage():           |
  |       |         patch_rootdir()            |
  |       |         inject_init_rc()           |
  |       |         start daemon               |
  |       |                                    |
  |       +--- [SAR] legacy_system_as_root():  |
  |       |     hexpatch /init                 |
  |       |     re-exec as magiskinit          |
  |       |                                    |
  |       +--- [RootFS] rootfs():              |
  |       |     patch_rw_root()                |
  |       |     inject services                |
  |       |                                    |
  |       +--- [Recovery] restore init         |
  |                                            |
  +------------------+-------------------------+
                     |
                     v
  [Android init starts]
       |
       v
  [init.rc executes injected services:]
       |
       +--> "magisk --post-fs-data"
       |     * Mount tmpfs at $MAGISKTMP
       |     * Initialize SELinux
       |     * Load and mount modules
       |     * Execute post-fs-data.d scripts
       |     * Check safe mode (volume down)
       |
       +--> "magisk --service" (late_start)
       |     * Execute service.d scripts
       |     * Start magiskd daemon socket
       |
       +--> "magisk --boot-complete"
             * Reset bootloop counter
             * Check manager APK
             * Broadcast ACTION_BOOT_COMPLETED
       |
       v
  [System fully booted]
       |
       v
  [magiskd runs as daemon, handles requests]
       |
       +--> su requests
       +--> Zygisk injection
       +--> DenyList enforcement
       +--> Module management
       +--> DB queries


7.3 SU Request Flowchart
---------------------------

  [User/app runs "su"]
       |
       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | su.cpp: su_client_main()                   |
  |   - Parse arguments (-c, -t, -Z, -g, -G)  |
  |   - Connect to magiskd via Unix socket     |
  |   - Create SuRequest { uid, context, ... } |
  |   - Send to daemon                         |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
                       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | daemon.rs: su_daemon_handler()             |
  |   - Receive SuRequest                      |
  |   - Lookup in su database (db.rs)          |
  |                                            |
  |   Permissions:                             |
  |     [ALLOW] -> proceed                     |
  |     [DENY]  -> reject, return error       |
  |     [QUERY] -> ask user (below)           |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
              [If QUERY]
                       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | connect.rs: IPC with Magisk app            |
  |   - Create FIFO pipe                       |
  |   - Launch app via am start with extras   |
  |   - App shows SuRequestDialog             |
  |   - User taps Allow/Deny                  |
  |   - Decision written to FIFO              |
  |   - Optional: remember forever            |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
              [If ALLOW]
                       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | su_daemon_handler() continued:            |
  |   - Fork child process                     |
  |   - In child:                              |
  |     * Switch to app's mount namespace      |
  |     * Set UID/GID (requested or app's)     |
  |     * Drop capabilities                    |
  |     * Set SELinux context                  |
  |     * Open PTY if interactive              |
  |     * Execute shell with -c command        |
  |   - In parent:                             |
  |     * Wait for child to exit               |
  |     * Send exit code back to client        |
  +--------------------------------------------+


7.4 Zygisk Architecture Flowchart
-------------------------------------

  [Zygote process starts]
       |
       v
  [Android: LoadNativeBridge(libzygisk.so)]
       |
       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | entry.cpp: NativeBridgeItf exposed         |
  |   - onLoad() -> hook_entry()               |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
                       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | hook.cpp: PLT Hooking                     |
  |   Hook dlclose: Prevent library unload    |
  |   Hook strdup:  Detect "ZygoteInit"       |
  |                                          |
  |   When strdup("ZygoteInit") detected:    |
  |     -> ZygiskInitializer.init()           |
  |        * Hook JNI methods:               |
  |          - nativeForkAndSpecialize()      |
  |          - nativeSpecializeAppProcess()   |
  |          - nativeForkSystemServer()       |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
                       v
  [Zygote forks new app process]
       |
       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | Hooked: nativeForkAndSpecialize()          |
  |  or nativeSpecializeAppProcess()          |
  |                                          |
  |   1. Pre-fork:                            |
  |      - Check denylist                     |
  |      - Get module list from zygiskd       |
  |      - Prepare module context             |
  |                                          |
  |   2. Allow fork to proceed                |
  |                                          |
  |   3. Post-fork (in child process):        |
  |      - If on denylist: revert_unmount()   |
  |        (unmount all Magisk tmpfs/mounts)  |
  |      - If not denylisted:                 |
  |        * Load Zygisk modules              |
  |        * Call module onAppSpecialize()    |
  |        * Setup root hiding                |
  |      - Hook pthread_attr_destroy          |
  |        (cleanup Zygisk, allow GC)         |
  +--------------------------------------------+


7.5 Module Mounting Flowchart
--------------------------------

  [Boot: post-fs-data stage]
       |
       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | module.rs: setup_modules()                |
  |   Scan /data/adb/modules/*/               |
  |                                            |
  |   For each module directory:               |
  |     Check module.prop (id, name, author)  |
  |     Check disable flag                    |
  |     Check remove flag                     |
  |     Read update.json if present            |
  |                                            |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
                       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | Build Virtual Filesystem Tree:            |
  |                                            |
  |   For each active module:                  |
  |     Walk module/system/*                   |
  |       For each file/dir:                   |
  |         If .replace flag:                  |
  |           -> Create whiteout (empty dir)   |
  |         Else:                              |
  |           -> Register for bind mount       |
  |     Walk module/vendor/* (same)            |
  |     Walk module/system_ext/* (same)        |
  |     Walk module/product/* (same)           |
  |                                            |
  |     Collect sepolicy.rule files            |
  |     Collect zygisk/*.so files              |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
                       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | Apply Bind Mounts:                        |
  |   For each registered replacement:        |
  |     - Create temp mount point             |
  |     - Bind mount module file over real    |
  |     - Ensure original is hidden           |
  |                                            |
  |   Inject Magisk bins:                      |
  |     - Bind magisk to /sbin/               |
  |     - Bind to /system/bin/                |
  |     - Inject into PATH directories        |
  |                                            |
  |   Inject Zygisk libs:                      |
  |     - Copy module zygisk/*.so to          |
  |       $MAGISKTMP/zygisk/                  |
  |     - These are mapped by zygiskd         |
  +--------------------------------------------+


7.6 DenyList Flowchart
--------------------------

  [DenyList configured in Magisk Manager]
       |
       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | deny/utils.cpp: add/remove/enable/disable |
  |   Lists are stored in SQLite DB            |
  |   Watches /data/system/packages.xml via    |
  |     inotify for app install/update/remove  |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
                       v
  [App on denylist is launched by Zygote]
       |
       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | Hooked: nativeForkAndSpecialize()         |
  |   Process name matched against denylist   |
  |                                            |
  |   If matched:                              |
  |     1. Set DENY flag on process context    |
  |     2. After fork:                         |
  |        -> revert_unmount()                 |
  |           * Unmount $MAGISKTMP             |
  |           * Unmount all module bind mounts  |
  |           * Unmount su/ contents           |
  |           * Hide magisk binaries           |
  |         OR                                 |
  |        -> umount_magisk()                  |
  |           * More aggressive unmounting     |
  |           * For system apps / GMS          |
  |                                            |
  |   Zygisk also patches logcat to filter     |
  |   magisk-related lines from denylisted     |
  |   processes (deny/logcat.cpp)              |
  +--------------------------------------------+


