  |  |    |    +-- updater-script           |
  |  |    +-- stub.apk                      |
  |  |                                        |
  |  +-- res/ (layouts, drawables, strings)  |
  |  +-- kotlin/ (Kotlin metadata)          |
  +--------------------------------------------+

  Note: Native binaries are RENAMED as lib*.so for JNI loading,
        but they are actually standalone executables, not shared libs.
        The naming convention allows Gradle to package them as JNI libs.


================================================================================
8. DATA FLOW DIAGRAMS
================================================================================

8.1 Magisk Daemon Socket IPC Protocol
---------------------------------------

  +----------+          +----------+          +-----------+
  |  Client  |          |  magiskd |          |  Thread   |
  | (su/app) |          | (main)   |          |  Pool     |
  +----+-----+          +----+-----+          +-----+-----+
       |                     |                      |
       |   connect()         |                      |
       |-------------------->|                      |
       |                     |                      |
       |   send(Request)     | accept()             |
       |-------------------->|--------------------->|
       |                     |                      |
       |                     | handle_request()      |
       |                     | magisk::<variant>()   |
       |                     |                      |
       |   recv(Response)    |                      |
       |<--------------------|                      |
       |                     |                      |

  Request Encoding (binary via Encodable trait):
    [code: u32][body length: u32][body: bytes]

  Request Codes:
    0x01  CHECK_VERSION     -> returns version struct
    0x02  POST_FS_DATA      -> triggers boot stage
    0x03  LATE_START        -> triggers boot stage
    0x04  BOOT_COMPLETE     -> triggers boot stage
    0x05  SUPERUSER         -> SuRequest in body
    0x06  SQLITE_CMD        -> SQL + params in body
    0x07  DENYLIST           -> DenyList action
    0x08  ZYGOTE_RESTART    -> restart notification
    0x09  REMOVE_MODULES    -> remove all modules
    0x0A  ZYGISK            -> zygiskd comm


8.2 Boot Image Patching Data Flow
------------------------------------

  [Stock boot.img]
       |
       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | 1. magiskboot unpack boot.img             |
  |    Extracts: kernel, ramdisk.cpio, dtb,   |
  |              second, extra, recovery_dtbo  |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
                       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | 2. magiskboot cpio ramdisk.cpio:          |
  |    - Test ramdisk format                   |
  |    - Backup original init                  |
  |    - Add magiskinit as init               |
  |    - Add overlay.d/sbin/magisk.xz         |
  |    - Add overlay.d/sbin/stub.xz           |
  |    - Add overlay.d/sbin/init-ld.xz        |
  |    - Strip verify/encrypt from fstab      |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
                       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | 3. magiskboot dtb dtb:                    |
  |    - Patch fstab in device tree            |
  |    - Remove verify flag                    |
  |    - Remove encrypt flag                   |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
                       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | 4. magiskboot repack new-boot.img         |
  |    - Reassemble boot image components     |
  |    - Preserve original header format      |
  |    - Optional: sign with AVB              |
  |    - Optional: add ChromeOS headers       |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
                       v
  [Patched boot.img (ready to flash)]


8.3 OTA Payload Extraction
-----------------------------

  [payload.bin]
       |
       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | 1. Parse protobuf metadata (payload.bin)  |
  |    - Read update_metadata proto            |
  |    - List partitions: boot, vbmeta, etc.  |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
                       v
  +--------------------------------------------+
  | 2. For each partition:                    |
  |    - Read operations list                  |
  |    - Handle operations:                    |
  |      * REPLACE, REPLACE_BZIP2             |
  |      * ZERO, DISCARD                      |
  |      * SOURCE_COPY                        |
  |    - Apply operations sequentially         |
  |    - Decompress if needed                  |
  +--------------------+-----------------------+
                       |
                       v
  [Extracted boot.img / vbmeta.img etc.]


